The '''1987 Daxing'anling Wildfire''' (大兴安岭特大森林火灾), also known as the '''May 6 Fire''' (5·6大火) was a major [[wildfire]] that began in the northeast [[Daxing'anling Prefecture]] [[Heilongjiang]] [[People's Republic of China]] on May 6, 1987.<ref name="chn">Chinanews.com. "[http://big5.chinanews.com.cn:89/special/guoqing/60/2009/06-24/114.shtml Chinanews.com]." ''大興安嶺特大森林火災.'' Retrieved on 2009-07-30.</ref>  The burning lasted almost a month, when it was finally stopped on June 2, 1987.<ref name="sohu">Sohu.com. "[http://news.sohu.com/20090506/n263790140.shtml Sohu.com]." ''1987年5月6日 大兴安岭发生特大火灾.'' Retrieved on 2009-08-01.</ref>  The fire covered about {{convert|10000|km2|acre}} of which 6500 square kilometres was forestry.<ref name="sohu" />  About 266 people were wounded and 211 died in the sea of fire with 50,000 left homeless.<ref name="chn" />  

