{{Infobox song contest |name = Melodifestivalen |year = 1974 |final = 9 February 1974 |presenters = [[Johan Sandström (presenter)|Johan Sandström]] |venue = [[SR Television Centre]], Stockholm, Sweden |vote = Regional juries |winner = "[[Waterloo (ABBA song)|Waterloo]]" by [[ABBA]] }}
[[Image:Abbamf74.JPG|thumb|200px|[[Anni-Frid Lyngstad]] and [[Agnetha Fältskog]] of ABBA.]]
'''[[Melodifestivalen]] 1974''' was the selection for the 15th song to represent [[Sweden]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest]]. It was the 14th time that this system of picking a song had been used. 10 songwriters were selected by [[Sveriges Radio|SR]] for the competition. The final was broadcast on [[SVT1|TV1]] but was not broadcast on radio. ABBA went on to win that year's Eurovision Song Contest in [[Brighton]], Sweden's first Eurovision win.
