{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=August 2018}} {{infobox music festival | music_festival_name = Ruhaniyat - The All India Sufi & Mystic Music Festival | image = File:Dervish.JPG | caption= | location = | years_active = 2001 - Present | founders = Banyan Tree Events | dates = Between November and March | website = [http://www.ruhaniyat.com/ http://www.ruhaniyat.com] }} '''Ruhaniyat – The All India Sufi & Mystic Music Festival ''' is a [[music festival]] held in across [[India]]. It is organised by [[Mumbai]]-based cultural organisation Banyan Tree Events between November and March every year. This [[Sufism|Sufi]] festival is one of the biggest of its kind, and is held in Mumbai, [[Delhi]], [[Bangalore]], [[Chennai]], [[Kolkata]], [[Pune]] and [[Hyderabad, India|Hyderabad]].<ref>{{cite web |author=Express News Service |url=http://www.expressindia.com/latest-news/ruhaniyat-brings-to-city-doctors-of-the-soul/388960/ |title=Ruhaniyat brings to city ‘doctors of the soul’ |publisher=Express India |date=2008-11-22 |accessdate=2012-02-19 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120619151215/http://www.expressindia.com/latest-news/ruhaniyat-brings-to-city-doctors-of-the-soul/388960/ |archivedate=2012-06-19 |df= }}</ref> Musicians from various parts of India &mdash; sufi [[Qawwali|qawwals]], mystic musicians, [[Kabir panth]]is, and [[Baul]]s &mdash; perform at the festival.<ref>[http://ruhaniyat.com/ ruhaniyat official website]</ref>
==History== The Ruhaniyat festival started in 2001, the brainchild of Mahesh Babu and Nandini Mahesh, the Directors of Banyan Tree Events, to promote sufi and mystic music has evolved into a prestigious event.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindu.com/mp/2009/01/12/stories/2009011250670400.htm |title=Metro Plus Hyderabad / Events : Ruhaniyat is back |publisher=The Hindu |date=2009-01-12 |accessdate=2012-02-19}}</ref>
==The festival== Ruhaniyat means ''Soulfulness''. The festival features the best of maestros in [[Classical music|classical]], [[Folk music|folk]] and [[sufi music]], discovered from the interiors of remote Indian villages, [[Turkey]], [[Egypt]], [[Syria]] etc.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindu.com/mp/2009/01/21/stories/2009012150760100.htm |title=Metro Plus Hyderabad / Events : Spiritual odyssey |publisher=The Hindu |date=2009-01-21 |accessdate=2012-02-19}}</ref>
==Performers== [[Parvathy Baul]], [[Warsi Brothers]], [[Ateeq Hussain Khan]], Jari Sufi compositions of Azan Fakir of [[Manipur]], Hafiza Begum Chaudhury, Kabirpanthis Prahlad Tippania from Devas in [[Madhya Pradesh]], Jagar music by Rakesh Bhatt, Vithal Rao etc.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/life/2007/03/02/stories/2007030200050300.htm |title=Business Line : Features / Life News |publisher=Thehindubusinessline.com |date= |accessdate=2012-02-19}}</ref>
